article.headline: Chattanooga 83, Furman 49
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. -- Gee McGhee scored 16 points, Eric Robertson had 14 off the bench and Chattanooga pulled away in the second half to beat Furman 83-49 on Thursday night. Farad Cobb had 12 points for the Mocs (11-16, 6-7 Southern Conference), who have won three of their past four after four-game losing streak. Colin Reddick and Stephen Croone scored 12 points each, with Croone grabbing nine rebounds, and Bryant Irwin had 10 points for the Paladins (6-18, 3-10), who have lost four in a row, six of their past seven and are 1-11 on the road. Chattanooga shot 34 of 77 from the field, while Furman was 19 of 51. Chattanooga led 15-7 on Martynas Bareika's jumper with 13:03 left on the way to a 39-27 advantage at halftime. The Mocs pushed their lead to 48-30 only 2:04 into the second half and pulled away for the easy victory.
